      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing on dignity and autonomy is the most essential lens because it transforms abstract legal text into a powerful tool for humanizing marginalized communities and holding power accountable. By centering these concepts, you teach students that the Constitution is not just a set of rules for the government's convenience, but a shield that protects the inherent worth of every individual against state overreach. This perspective empowers young people to see themselves as active participants in a system designed to safeguard freedom, rather than passive observers of arbitrary laws.",
      "source": "target",
